reviews.text: I come here once a week, the quality is everytime again surprising me. Even though it's fast to serve, the quality is quite high. Much higher than with any of the chains. I like their noodle soup a lot, the ingredients taste really fresh and the soup have strong flavor.
As a Malaysian, I have to say Super amazing and authentic prawn noodles. The curry laksa on the other hand tastes abit different. Not to my liking but still quite decent.

This is the place I go at least once a month because it is near my office. For those people who like spicy prawn soup, you will like it very much. The taste is strong. When I wrote this comment, I could still recall the tast of spicy prawn soup. They also have non spicy selections.
I’m not sure if I tasted the shrimp base in mine as it was quite spicy. Perhaps it’s just not my type. The toppings were not bad though. It’s reasonably priced too so that’s a plus
Nice authentic prawn noodles. Well worth a try if you are in tge area
